cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CL

The paper deals with data analytics and machine learning techniques applied to basketball trajectory prediction. The use of deep bidirectional LSTM and mixture density network is a clear indication of the involvement of deep learning and probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for data collection and analysis, which suggests the possibility of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a likely sub-category. The use of AI techniques for decision-making in basketball also makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves time series analysis, which suggests the possibility of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for generating multi-modal outputs, which suggests the possibility of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible sub-category.
